Jayshree approached me on behalf of Greg, Jason and Sean about two weeks ago 
to set up a meeting. I informed her at that time that we were in the throes 
of Phase 2 launch and that we were focussed on their LME products and that we 
should meet after Phase 2.

I have also exchanged voice mails on same with Sean and have had recent 
discussions with Bruce Garner on Steel, Enron Network Partners and Enron 
Metals and the relationship between them.

As you know, Amita has worldwide responsibility for metals on EnronOnline. 
Although the Steel group is under separate ownership from Aluminum and 
Copper, there is obviously a degree of overlap.

It is important that the Steel launch is coordinated with our other metals 
activities and that all the usual bases are covered (Marketing launch 
processes, commercial review of contracts, products and structure, regulatory 
compliance, application training, etc.).

I am planning to meet Greg and Sean next week in Houston to discuss the 
above, their launch timetable and coordination with an expressed desire to 
create an Enron Steel vertical.

Please do not do anything further until I have had an opportunity to meet 
Greg and Sean and have assigned someone to take responsibility for 
coordinating all of the launch elements and to act as a central point of 
contact.

Thanks,

Dave




