Subject: Steel

Andy-

We (Jennifer, Rob and I) just met with Greg Hermans who will be heading up 
the steel trading group here in the U.S (Jason Seigal and Sean Keenan were 
also present).  They want to start trading asap - we gathered all the initial 
information we would need to get the product type set up.  Here are the facts:

Financial products only (but he wants to offer physical products in the near 
future.  The issue is that back office logistics systems to physically move 
the product do not exist  - the same challenge the paper guys have).
We are not trading this product OTC yet
The GTC's and long descriptions are in draft format.  Harry Collins (Legal) 
is working on - Rob Cass has already talked to Harry and I think we are close 
on this
The key customer list consists of approx. 50 customers (450 additional) - we 
requested this by Friday so that Credit can get started.  I will send a note 
to Debbie Brackett tonight.  As you can imagine, most of these are customers 
we are not currently doing business with, and the steel industry has not been 
the most profitable the last few years, so I am not sure how many of these 
will even get approved.
Back office systems - they have not decided what they are going to use yet -  
Sitara, TAGG or some other system (really irrelevant for you, but we will 
bridge to whatever system they choose if the number of transactions warrant 
this)
They have not determined which index/publication they will use (most likely 
something called Metal Bulletin)
The first two product types will be Hot Rolled and Cold Rolled
All products will be offered in USD
We need to determine if the products will be offered by EIM or ENA - I am 
fairly sure it will be ENA, but we are discussing with legal.  Greg was not 
sure...


This may not be news to you, but just in case, I wanted to make sure you were 
in the loop.   Please let me know if you have any thoughts/concerns.

Thanks
Sheri












